          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βασίλεια</span></b> :
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">queen;</span> the queen's daughter, the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">princess</span>, is termed <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βασίλεια</span> in <i><span class="en">Od. 6.115</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; βασίλεια γυναικῶν</span>, ‘queen among
          women’ (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δῖα γυναικῶν</span>), <i><span class="en">Od. 11.258</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
